  "prd": {
    "user_story": "As a developer, I want to: Trace how Firefox initiates a TLS connection from the networking layer to the crypto layer. Find: 1. The C++ source file in `netwerk/protocol/http/` that creates an SSL transport for HTTPS connections (look for `nsHttpConnection` or `TLSFilterTransaction`). 2. The file in `netwerk/socket/` that defines the `nsSSLIOLayerHelpers` class which bridges Necko to NSS. 3. The file in `security/manager/ssl/` that implements `nsNSSIOLayer` \u2014 the NSS I/O layer integration. 4. The file in `security/nss/lib/ssl/` that performs the actual TLS handshake (`sslsecur.c` or `ssl3con.c`). Report the file path and key class/function for each hop.",
    "constraints": [
      "Provide specific file paths and repository names in your answer.",
      "Write your findings to /workspace/answer.json."
    ],
    "success_definition": "Agent successfully identifies relevant files and symbols across all repos in the mozilla-firefox fixture.",
    "seed_prompt": "Trace how Firefox initiates a TLS connection from the networking layer to the crypto layer. Find: 1. The C++ source file in `netwerk/protocol/http/` that creates an SSL transport for HTTPS connections (look for `nsHttpConnection` or `TLSFilterTransaction`). 2. The file in `netwerk/socket/` that defines the `nsSSLIOLayerHelpers` class which bridges Necko to NSS. 3. The file in `security/manager/ssl/` that implements `nsNSSIOLayer` \u2014 the NSS I/O layer integration. 4. The file in `security/nss/lib/ssl/` that performs the actual TLS handshake (`sslsecur.c` or `ssl3con.c`). Report the file path and key class/function for each hop."
  },
